# Psychologist SOP

  [bold]1.[/bold] The Psychologist may perform a full psychological evaluation on anyone, along with any potential treatment, provided the person in question seeks them out;

  [bold]2.[/bold] The Psychologist may [bold]not[/bold] force someone to receive therapy if the person does not want it. Exception is made for violent criminals and only if the [color=#cb0000]Head of Security[/color], [color=#cb0000]Magistrate[/color] or [color=#1b67a5]Captain[/color] orders it;

  [bold]3.[/bold] The Psychologist is [bold]not[/bold] permitted to administer any medication without consent from their patient;

  [bold]4.[/bold] The Psychologist is [bold]not[/bold] permitted to muzzle or straightjacket anyone without express permission from the [color=#1b67a5]Chief Medical Officer[/color], [color=#1b67a5]Captain[/color] , [color=#cb0000]Magistrate[/color], or [color=#cb0000]Head of Security[/color]. An exception is made for violent and/or out of control patients;

  [bold]5.[/bold] The Psychologist may recommend a patient's demotion if they find their psychological condition to render them unfit to fulfill their duties;

  [bold]6.[/bold] The Psychologist may request to consult prisoners in Permanent Imprisonment. This must happen inside the Brig, preferably inside the Permabrig, and only with [color=#cb0000]Warden[/color] and/or [color=#cb0000]Head of Security[/color] authorization. This should be done under the supervision of a member of [color=#cb0000]Security[/color] with Permabrig access.
